# Documentation Structure Rules

- Always structure documents using clear, hierarchical headings (H1–H4).
- Begin every document with an executive summary tailored to the audience.
- Maintain consistent formatting across all documents (headings, lists, tables).
- Use standardized sections for technical documents:
  - Overview
  - Objectives
  - Scope
  - Assumptions
  - Architecture / Design
  - Risks & Mitigations
  - Dependencies
  - Deliverables
  - Acceptance Criteria
  - Appendices
- Use tables for comparisons, compliance matrices, and requirement mappings.
- Ensure every section has complete, meaningful content; avoid placeholders.

